    Description:
    SHARE provides a no-cost evidence-based Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) diagnosis and rehabilitation for Post 9/11 military veterans, Active-Duty and Reserve/National Guard service members, and first responders who are ready to accept help and healing with TBI and other mental health concerns.

    This program provides:

    - Traumatic brain injury diagnosis and rehabilitation

    SHARE offers a selection of rehabilitation care and treatment that includes:

    - Intensive Outpatient (IOP) Treatment, Outpatient treatment
    - Neurology, Case Management, Occupational Therapy, Physical Therapy, Speech-Language Pathology, Behavioral Health, Recreation Therapy, Peer Support, and Transition Support for 12 months following graduation from the program.

    The program is available at no cost and offers each individual the opportunity to embark on a truly individualized and impactful path to renewed relationships, purpose, and life.

    Eligibility:
    Calling about a Veteran, and caller is trying to help the Veteran access care, especially mental health care.
    Availability:
    available
    Description:
    Coaching Into Care is a national telephone service of the U.S. Dept. of Veterans Affairs (VA) which aims to educate, support, and empower family members and friends who are seeking care or services for a Veteran. Our goal is to help Veterans, their family members, and other loved ones find the appropriate services at their local VA facilities and/or in their community.

    We also provide coaching to family and friends of Veterans who see that a Veteran in their life may be having difficulty adjusting to civilian life. Coaching is provided by licensed psychologists or social workers, free-of-charge. Coaching involves helping our callers figure out how to motivate the Veteran to seek treatment. We can help you get information about mental health, services at the VA and tips on how to begin the conversation about treatment with a loved one who is a Veteran.

    What to expect:

    When you call Coaching Into Care at 888-823-7458, you will talk with a member of our team who specializes in helping callers determine the best way to help the Veteran they care about and how to navigate the VA system. Our hours of operation are Monday — Friday, from 8 AM to 8 PM (Eastern).

    Calls with a coach vary in length, but generally take 10 to 30 minutes, depending on the issue. Our work with you may extend for several calls and usually with the same coach.

    Coaching Into Care takes your privacy, and that of the Veteran, very seriously. We keep all calls confidential, except for cases in which we act to protect the lives of you, the Veteran, or others.

    Print View
    Eligibility:
    • American Military Combat Veteran with moral injury.
    • Able to travel overseas.
    • Hold Passport.
    • Commitment to team for one year post trip.
    Availability:
    available
    Description:
    Heroes to Heroes Journey to Israel is a life-changing journey for combat veterans who are having challenges with moral injury, or having challenges returning to civilian life after their time serving our country. American veterans travel to Israel where they are joined by Israeli peers and this group travels, learns, and explores as a unit.

    Our program is designed to help our participants:

    -Develop social and emotional bonds with one another while exploring their spirituality and pushing themselves physically

    Heroes to Heroes requires a one-year commitment to the team. Each team will meet via Skype a minimum of every six (6) weeks post-journey for one year. Each team member is expected to commit to his or her team to support one another and be there for one another to help with transitioning back to civilian life. This is an extremely emotional journey, and the processing post-journey is critical. Team members must work together. All participants are expected to refrain from alcohol and, of course, recreational drugs throughout the journey. Participants must agree to give Heroes to Heroes a $520.00 refundable deposit (refunded on return to US ).

    The only cost to participants is for a U.S. Passport (must have an expiration date of six months or more post-journey), airfare to meet the team at the U.S. point of departure to Israel (usually either EWR (Newark Liberty, NJ), JFK, or LAX), and money for incidentals such as gifts and souvenirs.
    Languages:
    English
    Cost:
    Free

    Description:
    Star Legacy Foundation's Peer Companions program is available to anyone who would like to talk to someone who has experienced infant death. This program is open to and designed for all types of perinatal loss and available to all affected by the death of a baby.

    This program provides:

    - Peer support over phone, email, and text nationwide
    - In-person support available in limited areas (Minnesota and New York Metro)

    Additionally, the family support services are available to all affected by the death of a baby including parents, siblings, grandparents, aunts/uncles, other extended family, friends, and co-workers.

  • Peer Counseling

    by  Peer Collective
    Skip to next program
      Reviewed on: 12/17/2024
    Claimed Program This program has been claimed by Peer Collective and they are helping to ensure the information is accurate and up-to-date. Learn more.
    Peer Collective provides access to mental health support through our peer counselors who are highly skilled and empathetic listeners making emotional support affordable and available at the push...

    • peer support
    Serving

    Go to the program's website
    2547.05 miles ( serves nationwide)
    Serves nationwide
    Open Now : Open 24 Hours
    Print View
    Eligibility:
    Follow the Next Steps to find out if this program has eligibility criteria.
    Availability:
    available
    Description:
    Peer Collective provides access to mental health support through our peer counselors who are highly skilled and empathetic listeners making emotional support affordable and available at the push of a button.

    Services provided:

    - Peer counseling

    Our counselors have an incredible diversity of backgrounds and life experience, they also approach coping with and overcoming challenges in diverse ways. Some focus on listening and validating, while others focus on reframing situations or solving problems. There is no one-size-fits-all approach to life. The core of peer counseling is that the relationship is based on shared experience, rather than diagnosing and treating a mental illness. We’re open and transparent about the challenges we’ve faced, so you can find someone who can relate.

    We offer 30-minute online counseling sessions for just $14. This allows us to pay our counselors a living wage, while making emotional support as easy to access as possible. Sessions happen over Zoom, so they can be audio or video.

    Peer Collective counselors have passed our rigorous screening and demonstrate exceptional empathy, warmth, and understanding, but are not licensed therapists and don’t diagnose or treat mental disorders. Instead, their job is to support you in whatever way you want to be supported.
